<li>EvgS/EvgA induces the EvgA-YdeO-GadE cascade of AR gene regulation , and a branched pathway operating via SafA activates the PhoQ/PhoP system , leading to an enhanced level of cellular RpoS via IraM .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=21193607" target="_blank">21193607</a>]<br></li></div>
<li>Acid resistance in exponentially growing cells is induced by the overexpression of EvgA ( 18 , 25 , 39 ) and the activation of the sensor EvgS ( unpublished results ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=17998538" target="_blank">17998538</a>]<br></li>
<li>Since RpoS is a general stress response sigma factor , involved in responses to such stresses as starvation and high osmolarity , activation of the EvgS/EvgA system may induce responses to other stresses in addition to acid stress due to the enhanced level of cellular RpoS .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=21193607" target="_blank">21193607</a>]<br></li>
<li>Contribution of SafA to acid resistance conferred by EvgS / EvgA activation .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=21193607" target="_blank">21193607</a>]<br></li>
<li>Connector SafA contributes to acid resistance conferred by EvgS/EvgA activation by low pH in minimal medium .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=21193607" target="_blank">21193607</a>]<br></li>
<li>Besides the transcriptional cascade , EvgS/EvgA system activation also activates the PhoQ/PhoP system via the small membrane protein SafA .18 ) This pathway also contributes to acid resistance .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=19352034" target="_blank">19352034</a>]<br></li>
<li>Since the activation of the EvgS/EvgA system induces acid resistance , we examined whether the SafA-activated PhoQ/PhoP system is also involved in the acid resistance induced by EvgS/EvgA .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=21193607" target="_blank">21193607</a>]<br></li>
<li>Using a constitutively active evgS1 mutant for the activation of EvgS/EvgA , we found that SafA , PhoQ , and PhoP all contributed to the acid resistance phenotype .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=21193607" target="_blank">21193607</a>]<br></li>
<li>Therefore , the transcriptional activation of mgtA was not due to the activation of the EvgS/EvgA system by b1500 but to a PhoQ/PhoP-dependent pathway .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=17998538" target="_blank">17998538</a>]<br></li>
<li>Induction of iraM by EvgS/EvgA activation requires SafA , PhoP , and PhoQ and is directly regulated by PhoP .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=21193607" target="_blank">21193607</a>]<br></li>
<li>Thus , it was presumed that the activation of EvgS / EvgA increased the cellular RpoS level in a SafA-PhoQ/PhoP-dependent manner .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=21193607" target="_blank">21193607</a>]<br></li>
<li>Moreover , EvgS/EvgA activation resulted in the accumulation of cellular RpoS in the exponential-phase cells in a SafA - , PhoQ - , and PhoP-dependent manner .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=21193607" target="_blank">21193607</a>]<br></li>
<li>( A ) Accumulation of RpoS at the exponential phase by EvgS/EvgA activation requires SafA , PhoP , and PhoQ .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=21193607" target="_blank">21193607</a>]<br></li>
<li>Upregulation of RpoS-regulated genes by EvgS/EvgA activation .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=21193607" target="_blank">21193607</a>]<br></li>
<li>Induction of gadE by EvgS/EvgA activation involves RpoS .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=21193607" target="_blank">21193607</a>]<br></li>
<li>Accumulation of RpoS induced by EvgS/EvgA activation at the exponential phase requires SafA .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=21193607" target="_blank">21193607</a>]<br></li>
<li>We examined whether IraM was involved in the accumulation of RpoS induced by EvgS / EvgA activation at the exponential phase .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=21193607" target="_blank">21193607</a>]<br></li>
<li>Next , we checked whether iraM was actually induced by EvgS/EvgA activation .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=21193607" target="_blank">21193607</a>]<br></li>
<li>Transcripts induced by EvgS/EvgA activation are indicated by arrows .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=21193607" target="_blank">21193607</a>]<br></li>
<li>Another cascade of signal transduction , in which the phosphorylated EvgA activates the PhoPQ system followed by the up-regulation of tolC , was suggested ( Fig. 3 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=14523115" target="_blank">14523115</a>]<br></li>
<li>Promoter p2 appears to be activated by phosphorylated EvgA ( in a strain with a mutant evgS ) and PhoPQ together ( Eguchi et al. , 2003 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=18673442" target="_blank">18673442</a>]<br></li>
<li>Moreover , it is difﬁcult to interpret the transcriptional changes resulting from the overexpression : did it occur from the increased level of non-phosphorylated EvgA or from EvgA phosphorylated by sources other than its cognate sensor EvgS , such as acetyl phosphate ?	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=14523115" target="_blank">14523115</a>]<br></li>
<li>On the other hand , the increased amount of EvgA did not enhance the transcriptional level of evgA , which is transcribed divergently from emrK , neither in the absence nor in the presence of acetylphosphate .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=14523115" target="_blank">14523115</a>]<br></li>
<li>This fact suggests that EvgA may directly regulate yfdE , yfdW , yfdX , and ypdI as well as emrK .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=12670992" target="_blank">12670992</a>]<br></li>
