			<label class="collapse_EVO" for="_3"><font size="5px">EvgA evolution</font></label>
				<input id="_3" type="checkbox">
				<div class="EVO"><br><ul><li>The two-component regulators EvgS ( sensor-kinase ) and EvgA ( response regulator ) are highly homologous to the vir-ulence-related BvgAS system of Bordetella pertussis .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=15489450" target="_blank">15489450</a>]<br></li>
<li>EvgA exhibits sequence similarity to the BvgA gene regulator , which controls the expression of adhesins , toxins , and other virulence factors in Bordetella pertussis ( 1 , 18 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=11157960" target="_blank">11157960</a>]<br></li>
<li>Other represented functions in our dataset relate to sensing and stimulus responses , mostly proteins belonging to two component systems , such as ArcA , RcsB , CpxR and EvgA .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=25518064" target="_blank">25518064</a>]<br></li>
