<li>These results suggest that yhiE is essential for acid resistance induced by YdeO overexpression and that EvgA overexpression induces yhiE via the induction of YdeO .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=12694615" target="_blank">12694615</a>]<br></li>
<li>These results are similar to our previous observation that EvgA overexpression does not confer acid resistance to the ydeP-b1500-ydeO deletion strain , and are consistent with the hypothesis that YdeO induces yhiE expression .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=12694615" target="_blank">12694615</a>]<br></li>
<li>The ﬁrst class contains seven operons induced by EvgA overexpression in the absence of ydeO , an AraC/XylS regulator gene .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=12694615" target="_blank">12694615</a>]<br></li>
<li>This acid resistance was eliminated by the deletion of ydeP , ydeO , or gadE , genes induced by EvgA overexpression .11 ) Microarray analysis identiﬁed two classes of operons or genes .12 ) The ﬁrst class contains seven operons or genes induced by EvgA overexpression in the absence of ydeO , encoding an AraC-like regulator .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=19352034" target="_blank">19352034</a>]<br></li>
<li>EvgA overexpression induced the expression of ydeO , an AraC/XylS regulator , indicating that some of the genes induced by EvgA overexpression might be directly induced by YdeO instead of EvgA .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=12399493" target="_blank">12399493</a>]<br></li>
<li>Operons or genes in the second class were induced by EvgA overexpression only in the presence of ydeO , which suggests the following model of the regulatory network of the acid resistance genes : EvgA directly upregulates operons or genes containing ydeO in the ﬁrst class and indirectly upregulates operons or genes in the second class containing gadE , a LuxR-family regulator gene , via YdeO .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=19352034" target="_blank">19352034</a>]<br></li>
<li>The expressions of three efﬂux pump genes , emrK , yhiU , and yhiV , were signiﬁcantly induced by EvgA overexpression , as shown in Table 3 .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=12399493" target="_blank">12399493</a>]<br></li>
<li>This conserved motif can be detected in the upstream regions of several highly induced genes ( ydeP , b1500 , yegR , emrK , yfdX and yfdW ) by overexpression of EvgA .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=14523115" target="_blank">14523115</a>]<br></li>
<li>Altogether , microarray analysis allowed the identiﬁcation of 12 genes induced by EvgA overexpression in the ydeO deletion strain , ydeP-b1500 , yegR-b2084-yegZ , emrKY and yfdXWUVE ( Table 1 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=12694615" target="_blank">12694615</a>]<br></li>
<li>A. Sequences found upstream of the genes induced by EvgA overexpression in the ydeO deletion strain .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=12694615" target="_blank">12694615</a>]<br></li>
<li>Of 30 genes induced more than eightfold by EvgA overexpression , 18 , including ydePO and yhiE , are also induced by H-NS deletion .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=12399493" target="_blank">12399493</a>]<br></li>
<li>Because we were primarily interested in genes induced by EvgA overexpression , we did not give further consideration to the gene repressed by EvgA overexpression .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=12694615" target="_blank">12694615</a>]<br></li>
<li>Operons in the second class were induced by EvgA overexpression only in the presence of ydeO .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=12694615" target="_blank">12694615</a>]<br></li>
<li>induced by EvgA overexpression .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=12694615" target="_blank">12694615</a>]<br></li>
<li>AppY regulates the appCBA operon ( 5 ) , which was induced by EvgA overexpression .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=12399493" target="_blank">12399493</a>]<br></li>
<li>The expression of gadX was 1.7 - to 4.9-fold induced by EvgA overexpression , and the changes were signiﬁcant in all four comparisons ( http://arep.med.harvard.edu/cgi-bin/Express DBecoli/EXDStart ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=12399493" target="_blank">12399493</a>]<br></li>
<li>The tolC homologues yjcP , yohG , and ylcB ( 35 ) showed no signiﬁcant change in expression by EvgA overexpression .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=12399493" target="_blank">12399493</a>]<br></li>
<li>yhiW , appY , and adiY showed no signiﬁcant change by EvgA overexpression except that the expression of yhiW was signiﬁcantly induced 28-fold by IPTG in the evgAS strain harboring pQEevgA .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=12399493" target="_blank">12399493</a>]<br></li>
<li>Figure 9A illustrates , using a Northern blot , that ydeO is also acid induced and that EvgA is needed to activate ydeO expression .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=15489450" target="_blank">15489450</a>]<br></li>
<li>Overexpression of either EvgA or GadX induced the expression of gadA , gadBC , and hdeABD .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=12399493" target="_blank">12399493</a>]<br></li>
<li>The gadX promoter , which is not activated by GadE or ( unlike all the above promoters ) by induction via EvgA but does require RpoS for induction by low pH ( 1 ) , also showed signiﬁcantly reduced acid-induced expression in the rcsB strain ( Table 1 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=21571995" target="_blank">21571995</a>]<br></li>
<li>The ompA deletion mutant is signiﬁcantly more sensitive than that of its parent strain to acidic environment and high osmolarity ( 47 ) , and the expression of this gene was induced by EvgA overproduction .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=12670992" target="_blank">12670992</a>]<br></li>
<li>The EvgS/EvgA system is activated in strain MG1655/pOH2001D52A , whereas it is inactivated in MG1655 evgA/pOH2001D52A because EvgA in this strain can not be phosphorylated by the activated EvgS .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=19352034" target="_blank">19352034</a>]<br></li>
<li>Expression of the b1500 gene is directly regulated by the EvgS/EvgA system , and b1500 expression from a heterologous promoter simultaneously activated the expression of mgtA and other PhoP regulon genes .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=17998538" target="_blank">17998538</a>]<br></li>
<li>When the EvgS/EvgA system was activated by the evgS1 mutation , mgtA expression was enhanced ( Fig. 2 A and B , column 3 ) as reported ( 10 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=17998538" target="_blank">17998538</a>]<br></li>
<li>The expression of ydeO is activated by the two-component system EvgSA [ 9,10,11 ] , forming a regulatory cascade , EvgA .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=25375160" target="_blank">25375160</a>]<br></li>
<li>Expression of mgrB is also activated by the EvgS-EvgA two-component system in a PhoP-dependent manner ( 11 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=19734312" target="_blank">19734312</a>]<br></li>
<li>Since the PhoQ/PhoP system induces expression of AR genes gadW and hdeA ( 33 ) , we focused on whether connector SafA played a role in the acid resistance conferred by the EvgS/EvgA system .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=21193607" target="_blank">21193607</a>]<br></li>
<li>These data indicate that the EvgS/EvgA system regulates the expression of acid resistance genes ( Fig. 6 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=17998538" target="_blank">17998538</a>]<br></li>
<li>These results indicate that both EvgS / EvgA and PhoQ/PhoP are involved in the expression of acid resistance genes .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=17998538" target="_blank">17998538</a>]<br></li>
<li>Moreover , enhanced transcription of the phoPQ genes did not further activate expression of the PhoQ/PhoP regulated genes , and no EvgA binding consensus sequence ( 12 , 18 ) was found in the promoter regions of the PhoP regulon genes .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=17998538" target="_blank">17998538</a>]<br></li>
<li>This regulatory network between the two systems also occurred as a result of overproduction of the EvgA regulator ; however , enhanced transcription of the phoPQ genes did not further activate expression of the PhoP/PhoQ-regulated genes .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=15126461" target="_blank">15126461</a>]<br></li>
<li>However , it is not clear what purpose this regulation serves in vivo since several studies have shown that EvgA can activate the gadE promoter in a ydeO mutant .24,26 GadE directly activates its own expression while repressing production of YdeO .24 Many structural genes within the AFI , as well as the gadBC locus , are activated directly by GadE , although effectors such as slp appear not to be under GadE control .15,18,27 The contribution of the alternate general stress and stationary phase sigma factor RpoS may also have a role under low pH inducing conditions , since GadE positive feedback can be further supported by its presence .28 The homologous transcription factors * Corresponding author .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=20603130" target="_blank">20603130</a>]<br></li>
<li>Chromosomal knockout mutations indicate the system is a branched control circuit ( diagrammatically summarized in the Discussion ) where EvgA activates gadE expression directly and indirectly through a ydeO feed-forward loop and where gadE autoregulates its own expression .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=15489450" target="_blank">15489450</a>]<br></li>
<li>It has been reported that EvgA also directly induces GadE expression , forming a branched pathway of regulation ( 40 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=17998538" target="_blank">17998538</a>]<br></li>
<li>These results also conﬁrm that EvgA affects gadE expression in YdeO-dependent and - independent pathways .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=15489450" target="_blank">15489450</a>]<br></li>
<li>Next we tested whether EvgA and YdeO affected gadE expression under physiological conditions .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=15489450" target="_blank">15489450</a>]<br></li>
<li>However , neither EvgA nor YdeO is required for gadE expression in stationary phase .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=17660422" target="_blank">17660422</a>]<br></li>
<li>The pUC19 vectors , pUCevgA and pQEevgA , which are constitutive and conditional EvgA expression plasmids , respectively , were transformed into the evgAS and acrB evgAS strains by electroporation .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=12399493" target="_blank">12399493</a>]<br></li>
<li>These results are consistent with the microarray data and suggest that EvgA binds to the six consensus sequences in the genome to induce the expression of ydeP , b1500-ydeO , yegR-b2084-yegZ , emrKY , evgAS , yfdX and yfdWUVE .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=12694615" target="_blank">12694615</a>]<br></li>
<li>Since EvgA is known to positively regulate emrKY gene expression ( 5 ) , we cloned emrKY into the pQE30 expression vector and observed that E. coli cells overexpressing EmrKY acquire resistance only to deoxycholate ( eightfold ) ( Table 1 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=11914367" target="_blank">11914367</a>]<br></li>
<li>EvgA affects the expression of gene clusters located near emrKY and yhiUV .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=12670992" target="_blank">12670992</a>]<br></li>
<li>EvgA binds the intergenic region of evgAS and emrKY and regulates the expression of both operons ( 13 , 36 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=12399493" target="_blank">12399493</a>]<br></li>
